        "timestamp": 1584562536
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"126931\">centril</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/227806-t-compiler.2Fwg-prioritization/topic/pre-meeting.20triage.202020-03-19.20.2354818/near/191035595\" title=\"#narrow/stream/227806-t-compiler.2Fwg-prioritization/topic/pre-meeting.20triage.202020-03-19.20.2354818/near/191035595\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I have an idea re. speeding up beta nominations...: we can cc t-compiler and do straw polls on the merged PR itself</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>this isn't a bad idea, though I do wonder whether its effectiveness will depend on how far ahead of time pre-triage happens.</p>",
        "id": 191036097,
        "sender_full_name": "pnkfelix",
        "timestamp": 1584562637
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>e,g,</p>",
        "id": 191036109,
        "sender_full_name": "pnkfelix",
        "timestamp": 1584562643
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>will it act as impetus to do pre-triage 48 hours ahead of time, say?</p>",
        "id": 191036124,
        "sender_full_name": "pnkfelix",
        "timestamp": 1584562655
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>(not that that would be a bad thing. Just different.)</p>",
        "id": 191036138,
        "sender_full_name": "pnkfelix",
        "timestamp": 1584562663
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"116083\">@pnkfelix</span> my thinking was we would start the poll when we slap beta-nominated</p>",
        "id": 191036149,
        "sender_full_name": "centril",
        "timestamp": 1584562671
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>ah okay</p>",
        "id": 191036163,
        "sender_full_name": "pnkfelix",
        "timestamp": 1584562678
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>so it might give many days notice</p>",
        "id": 191036222,
        "sender_full_name": "centril",
        "timestamp": 1584562697
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>the one other issue</p>",
        "id": 191036230,
        "sender_full_name": "pnkfelix",
        "timestamp": 1584562703
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I wouldn't necessarily jump to beta-accepted based on the straw polls</p>",
        "id": 191036248,
        "sender_full_name": "pnkfelix",
        "timestamp": 1584562713
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I guess the main issue is that sometimes, in the synchronous meetings, someone raises a point that causes the group to sway their opinion</p>",
        "id": 191036309,
        "sender_full_name": "pnkfelix",
        "timestamp": 1584562743
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>sure; I think that's important for more subtle nominations, but often it's just a delay_span_bug thing</p>",
        "id": 191036353,
        "sender_full_name": "centril",
        "timestamp": 1584562774
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>(this is largely a reason why I still see a benefit in continuing to process the beta-noms synchronously...)</p>",
        "id": 191036356,
        "sender_full_name": "pnkfelix",
        "timestamp": 1584562776
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>true</p>",
        "id": 191036366,
        "sender_full_name": "pnkfelix",
        "timestamp": 1584562784
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>my thinking is that the \"I am opposed\" would be the more important signals during the async polling proccess</p>",
        "id": 191036445,
        "sender_full_name": "centril",
        "timestamp": 1584562810
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I sorta get the feeling right now that the beta-nomination process consists of a lot of dead time, where no one says anything, and you wait for folks to +1/-1</p>",
        "id": 191036599,
        "sender_full_name": "centril",
        "timestamp": 1584562897
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>well; that time also involves reading the diff of a PR and whatnot, but people could prepare for that async</p>",
        "id": 191036708,
        "sender_full_name": "centril",
        "timestamp": 1584562936
    }
